Title: Nordic Care Foot Care Cream(946 ml)
Description: The Swedish Foot Care Cream is extremely effective in the control of dry skin and cracked heels. It combines the skin's own natural moisturizer, Urea with the water-binding properties of Lactic Acid and Glycerin to leave skin feeling soft and supple. Excellent for softening and reducing the appearance of calluses and soothing the uncomfortable itch associated with dry skin. Antiseptic and soothing Eucalyptus Oil provides a subtle, natural fragrance. Hypoallergenic and Lanolin-free... Safe for Diabetics. Directions: Initially apply twice daily to clean, dry skin. Then apply as necessary. Key Ingredients Eucalyptus - long used in traditional remedies, Eucalyptus is considered one of the most powerful and versatile botanicals available. Has antiseptic, antibacterial and blood-circulating properties. Glycerin - has superb water-binding properties that allow it to draw and absorb water from the air. Helps retain moisture and break down intercellular blockage in the skin. Lactic Acid - a component of the skin's own natural moisturizing factor and an excellent exfoliant as well. Benefits include reduction of fine lines and wrinkles, lightening of skin pigmentation and softer, smoother skin with improved hydration. Urea - regarded as a true moisturizer since it attracts and retains moisture in the surface layer of the skin. Anti-inflammatory, antiseptic, and deodorizing properties allow it to protect the skin against harmful and damaging elements. Urea has been found to increase the absorption of other active ingredients, relieve itch and help skin feel soft and supple. Size : 32 oz / 960 ml

Title: Pretty Clean Soap Coffee Bean and Hemp Seed Oil Exfoliating Soap Level 4 - Nutty Coffee Scent(162 ml)
Description: The Pretty Clean Soap (PCS) Coffee Bean and Hemp Seed Oil Exfoliator is an extreme exfoliator and not for the timid! Best used on the legs and tush for silky smooth results, coffee grounds not only sand away rough patches, they have also been proven to dehydrate cellulite. Complete your "smooth booty" treatment by moisturizing with deep penetrating Hemp seed oil, to draw the anti-cellulite properties further into your skin. WHY EXFOLIATE? Our bodies are comprised of roughly 300 million skin cells. Every minute, healthy skin should shed up to 40,000 of those cells and replace them with healthy, glowing new cells. Properly maintained skin has the ability to recycle itself weekly. Exfoliating will slough away layers of dead skin cells, promote new cell growth and even skin tone. At Pretty Clean, we concentrate on enzyme and manual exfoliation. COFFEE BEAN BENEFITS: manual exfoliator, cellulite reducer, anti-inflammatory, wrinkle reducer, toning, odor remover, UV protection, activates skin circulation. Treats cellulite, varicose veins, rosacea HEMP SEED OIL BENEFITS: deep penetrating oil, anti-inflammatory, wrinkle reducer, antioxidant, skin balancer. Treats acne, psoriasis, eczema, minor abrasions EXFOLIATION LEVELS- LEVEL 1: For skin too sensitive for manual exfoliation, we offer a mild enzymatic alternative with the seaweed/shea butter bar. Not only does it gently deteriorate the bonds between your new and old skin, enzymes are deeply penetrating and clean inside each pore LEVEL 2: Light manual exfoliation, perfect for the face. Our Adzuki Bean and rice bran oil (or "Geisha Bar") recipe was derived from an ancient Japanese skin treatment, dating back to 600ce. LEVEL 3: Heavier manual exfoliation, for the body. The poppyseed and macadamia nut oil bar gives a buttery twist to a popular exfoliator LEVEL 4: Our most intense exfoliator. The coffee bean and hemp oil bar is a part of our cellulite busting system and should be used on the legs, thighs and tush.

Usage of the Black African Soap Break off a bar-size piece from the bulk, then press it to shape with your hands, or use it as is. It must be stored in a dry location or in a sealed plastic bag or it will become soft as it absorbs moisture. Black soap exposed to the air will have a thin white colored film. This film is not mold it is caused by absorption of water from the air. This can be avoided by keeping the soap in a dry location away from moisture until ready for use.
